translated: Frick, Erik, lawyer, Lerum, b. 7/6/04 in Gothenburg to councilor Ernst F. and Klara Jagenburg. Married in 1933 to Leila Engfeldt. Children: Birgitta b. 1937, Gunilla Christina b. 1939. Education: graduated from Gothenburg Latin School in 1923, graduated with a law degree from Stockholm University in 1928. Worked as a court clerk in Marks court from 1928-1931, clerked at Gothenburg City Hall from 1931-1932, worked at William Kristensen's law firm in Gothenburg in 1932, assistant lawyer at Arvid Schulz and Gunnar Dellborg's law firm in Gothenburg in 1932, and at Gunnar Dellborg's law firm in Gothenburg from 1936. Member of the Swedish Bar Association since 1936.
